  "poem_title": "Chingda Satpi",
  "language": "Manipuri",
  "original_poem": "चिंगदा सत्तपी मतोइ,  \nइचि याड्रीगु पमलैममा।  \nथावा थामा मनिन्बरी,  \nना थाम्बा चिंग्लई पंबीगु।\n\nइशिंगै बा फिनिनबा,  \nमरिंगाओबा नीनतंगोई।  \nताओई रेनबा नैरेइबा,  \nयामलंबा मरोमली ओइ।\n\nचिंग्दा फुरम्बा लाईगुम,  \nनुंगी दरेइ, चिंग्लई थाबी।  \nपोरं कांगरे, पंगक लेइबा,  \nफुरंबी लाई मरंगलाओ।",
  "translated_poem": "The flower of the hill, so fair and bright,  \nReaching for the sky in pure delight.  \nIts petals whisper a song untold,  \nOf the mountain’s love in the quiet fold.\n\nThe morning dew kisses its face,  \nIn this high, untouched, and sacred place.  \nWinds of time may come and go,  \nBut in this bloom, love will grow.\n\nThe hill’s flower sways in the breeze,  \nIn the shadow of ancient trees.  \nIt stands tall, proud and free,  \nA symbol of eternity.",
